definitions.definition: A stream that flows out, such as from a lake or reservoir; an outflow ; effluence .
examples: The landscape was dotted with reservoirs and many many effluent streams.

definitions.definition: Sewage or waste water discharged into a natural body of water.
examples: Residents have little control over the industrial effluent that pollutes their rivers.

main_definition: ( countable ) A stream that flows out, such as from a lake or reservoir; an outflow ; effluence .
secondary_definitions: ( uncountable ) Sewage or waste water discharged into a natural body of water.
